                    {
                        latin: '<span style="font-family:\'Roboto Mono\',monospace;font-style:italic">mos maiorum</span>',
                        translation: '"The custom of the ancestors" — the unwritten code of behaviour and precedent that governed Roman political life.',
                        analysis: 'The entire Gracchan crisis can be understood as a failure of <span style="font-family:\'Roboto Mono\',monospace;font-style:italic">mos maiorum</span>. The system works only as long as all parties accept its constraints. Once one side — whether the Gracchi or the Senate — decides that its goals are more important than customary limits, the system has no enforcement mechanism except social pressure, and social pressure fails when the stakes are high enough.'
                    }
